com.ihealth.communication.control

Class UpgradeProfile

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.ihealth.communication.control.UpgradeProfile

  • public abstract class UpgradeProfile
extends java.lang.Object
    Public APIs for the Upgrade serials device profiles

    Clients need to calliHealthDevicesManager.registerClientCallback(com.ihealth.communication.manager.iHealthDevicesCallback) register. When new data from Upgrade device, The Callback{#iHealthDevicesCallback #onDeviceNotify} will be triggered.

      static java.lang.String DEVICE_FINISH_UP_FLAG
      The key of the upgrade result.
      Value:
      0 indicates transmit successfully. 1 indicates upgrade successfully(MCU write and verify after successful) or upgrade pause. 2 indicates upgrade failed(Receive data error or timeout, no reply received). 3 indicates upgrade failed(Burn written MCU error). 4 indicates rollback success. Note:
      If the value is 0, indicates transmit successfully, device will upgrade itself. If the value is 1 and DEVICE_UP_MODE == 100 or 101, it indicates upgrade successfully. If the value is 1 and DEVICE_UP_MODE == 200, it indicates upgrade pause. If the value is 2,3,4, it indicates upgrade failed.

      }
      static java.lang.String DEVICE_UP_ERROR
      The key of the error code of upgrade.
      Value:
      100 Device type does not support. 102 Query device firmware information instruction timeout. 103 The init method is not called. 200 indicates network error. 201 Failed to get the next machine information 300 indicates device connection error. 301 indicates device stop upgrade. 400 indicates no need to upgrade. 401 The AppSecret is wrong. 402 The info file not exist. 403 The crc is null. 404 The crc is wrong. 405 The model is wrong. 406 The firmware file is incomplete. 500 Incorrect input parameter.
      static java.lang.String DEVICE_UP_FLAG
      The key of the device upgrade status.
      Value:
      0 indicates it's ready to upgrade 1 indicates low power, not allow to upgrade.

      • DEVICE_FINISH_UP_FLAG

        public static final java.lang.String DEVICE_FINISH_UP_FLAG
        The key of the upgrade result.
        Value:
        • 0 indicates transmit successfully.
        • 1 indicates upgrade successfully(MCU write and verify after successful) or upgrade pause.
        • 2 indicates upgrade failed(Receive data error or timeout, no reply received).
        • 3 indicates upgrade failed(Burn written MCU error).
        • 4 indicates rollback success.
        Note:
        • If the value is 0, indicates transmit successfully, device will upgrade itself.
        • If the value is 1 and DEVICE_UP_MODE == 100 or 101, it indicates upgrade successfully.
        • If the value is 1 and DEVICE_UP_MODE == 200, it indicates upgrade pause.
        • If the value is 2,3,4, it indicates upgrade failed.
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

        • 102 Query device firmware information instruction timeout.
        • 103 The init method is not called.
        • 200 indicates network error.
        • 201 Failed to get the next machine information
        • 300 indicates device connection error.
        • 301 indicates device stop upgrade.
        • 400 indicates no need to upgrade.
        • 401 The AppSecret is wrong.
        • 402 The info file not exist.
        • 403 The crc is null.
        • 404 The crc is wrong.
        • 405 The model is wrong.
        • 406 The firmware file is incomplete.
        • 500 Incorrect input parameter.
